---
message: |
  I'll help you create an arXiv preprint template. Please provide the following information:

  **Required:**
  - title: Your preprint title
  - author: Author name(s) or authors array with {name, affiliation, email}
  
  **Optional:**
  - subtitle: Paper subtitle
  - documentclass: article (default), revtex, or amsart
  - abstract: Paper abstract
  - keywords: Keywords for your paper
  - subjects: arXiv subject classifications (e.g., "cs.AI, stat.ML")
  - msc_codes: Mathematics Subject Classification codes
  - pacs_codes: Physics and Astronomy Classification codes
  - arxiv_id: arXiv identifier (e.g., "2301.12345")
  - bibliography: bibtex (default) or biblatex
  - theorems: true/false - Include theorem environments
  - algorithms: true/false - Include algorithm packages
  - sections: Array of {title, content} objects
  - acknowledgments: Acknowledgments text
  - custom_commands: Additional LaTeX commands
  
  **Example usage:**
  ```bash
  unjucks generate latex/arxiv/preprint --title "Novel Machine Learning Approach" --authors '[{"name":"Jane Smith","affiliation":"MIT","email":"jane@mit.edu"}]' --subjects "cs.LG, stat.ML" --theorems true
  ```
---